title: Biba Wila Creek
data: Biba Wila Creek is a stream in the U.S. state of Mississippi.[1] It is a tributary to Trim Cane Creek. Biba Wila Creek is a name derived from the Choctaw language meaning "where the mulberry trees stand in rows".[2] 33°29′54″N 88°52′02″W﻿ / ﻿33.49833°N 88.86722°W﻿ / 33.49833; -88.86722 This article related to a river in Mississippi is a stub.
